Filter disturbance data to predator presences

Source: R/summarise_dist.R
filter_predation.Rd

filter_predation(data)

Arguments

data

A dataframe with column "disturbance_cause", e.g. the ouput of wastd_GET("turtle-nest-disturbance-observations") parse_encounterobservations() or data("wastd_data"); wastd_data$nest_dist

Value

The dataframe with rows matching predator presences.

See also

Other wastd: add_nest_labels(), disturbance_by_season(), filter_alive(), filter_dead(), filter_disturbance(), ggplot_track_success_by_date(), ggplot_track_successrate_by_date(), hatching_emergence_success_area(), hatching_emergence_success_site(), hatching_emergence_success(), list_survey_count(), list_survey_effort(), map_dist(), map_mwi(), map_nests(), map_tracks(), nesting_type_by_area_season_age_species(), nesting_type_by_area_season_species(), nesting_type_by_season_age_species(), nesting_type_by_season_calendarday_age_species(), nesting_type_by_season_calendarday_species(), nesting_type_by_season_day_species(), nesting_type_by_season_species(), nesting_type_by_season_week_age_species(), nesting_type_by_season_week_site_species(), nesting_type_by_season_week_species(), nesting_type_by_site_season_age_species(), nesting_type_by_site_season_species(), parse_animal_encounters(), parse_area_sf(), parse_area(), parse_encounterobservations(), parse_surveys(), parse_turtle_nest_encounters(), plot_survey_count(), plot_survey_effort(), print.wastd_api_response(), summarise_hatching_and_emergence_success(), survey_count_heatmap(), survey_count(), survey_ground_covered(), survey_hours_heatmap(), survey_hours_per_person(), survey_hours_per_site_name_and_date(), survey_season_site_stats(), survey_season_stats(), survey_show_detail(), surveys_per_site_name_and_date(), track_success_by_species(), track_success(), tracks_ts()
